    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Structure used to return the time from TE_GetTime() The time is returned in seconds and nanoseconds. In Linux for example, we have the time utility. Using &quot;time ls&quot; command we get: real 0m0.002s (corresponds to wallClock) user 0m0.000s (Sum of all threads, corresponds to times.userTime) sys 0m0.000s (Sum of all threads, corresponds to times.kernelTime) </para>
    </detaileddescription>
